headline: U.S. Energy Leaders Praise Pact, but Fear Damage From Tariffs
abstract: Oil and gas companies may see an export revival from the accord, but they seek commitments that tariffs will be dropped.
lead_paragraph: HOUSTON â€” The American energy industry offered cautious praise Wednesday for the signing of an initial trade deal with China, but executives expressed disappointment that it seemed to lack a commitment to remove Chinese tariffs that have hampered their sales over the last two years.
